Thornwood

Necrotic estate-forest south of the Great Northern Forest canopy edge. Originally a fortified manor established by the Harren Charter during Midgaard's Founding Generation. Now a fused entity: manor and forest merged into a single predatory ecology that treats death as input.

Four governing logics: manorial (gates, titles, hereditary protocols), funerary (barrows, charnel verges, bone-processing cycles), forest (root pressure, adaptive pathing, canopy suppression), and substrate (pre-human crystalline geological formation that mediates the necrotic ecology).

The Harren Charter displaced ridge-clan burial customs (face-down oathbreaker graves, thorn-ring containment growth). The estate became Midgaard's overflow death-processing facility. Ritual specialists became production foremen.

The Root Covenant formed among the estate's lowest laborers. Core beliefs: confession spoken into earth at root-contact points, blood opens listening channels, roots carry memory, bone remembers debt. Lord Harren gave them administrative power and commissioned crystal cave exploration beneath the estate.

The Reversal Event followed. Roots grew toward ritual sites from hundreds of meters away. The dead rose with bark-textured skin and thorn-growth through joints. The forest replicated manor blueprints in biological material.

Lord Harren was retained as an estate revenant -- fully aware, trapped in the system he created. The Thornwood Lich emerged from the substrate itself, a geological intelligence. Its biological binding is failing. The Wild Hunt, the estate's mobile enforcement arm, has extended patrol range toward the Lantern Road farther than any prior generation.

