Thornwood -- Midgaard Perspective

Source: Bureau of Northern Perimeter, Containment and Liability Division.

Thornwood is a failed Midgaard charter estate. The Harren Charter is on file (parchment thirty-one, northern estates drawer), authorized by the First Stone Accord. It tasked a fortified manor with processing war dead. Quarterly reports ran for six generations, then stopped.

The Root Covenant was a containment failure. Substrate theology born among estate laborers, rejecting chapel oversight. Lord Harren invited them into administration with no oversight audit and commissioned crystal cave exploration with no risk assessment. The Reversal Event was unaudited institutional transformation.

Lord Harren retained as estate revenant. The Thornwood Lich classified as a failed charter officer operating beyond mandate. The Wild Hunt has pushed patrol range toward the Lantern Road. Hunt outriders sighted within three miles of waystone fourteen.

Current protocol: doubled patrols between waystones twelve and eighteen, quarterly perimeter audits, standing advisory against solo travel south of the canopy edge. The Bureau has petitioned for a containment expedition four consecutive cycles. The Ledgerhouse has approved none, citing insufficient precedent for charter revocation of a self-sustaining necrotic estate.

The Reckoning faction has requested public reading of the Harren Charter eleven times. Root Covenant phrases appear in Reckoning pamphlets. The Continuity faction calls Thornwood an anomaly. The Reckoning faction calls it a ledger entry that grew roots.

