Thornwood -- Mafdet Perspective

Source: Quarantine Ledger, Necrotic Expansion Hazard, Watch Status.

Thornwood is not a direct threat to Mafdet trade corridors currently. The Hazard Scribes project it will become one. The Lantern Road -- the artery feeding goods into oasis corridors and eventually Mafdet's docks -- passes through the Great Northern Forest near Thornwood. If Thornwood contacts the Road, the supply chain contracts.

The estate's assimilation behavior elevates it above ordinary hazard. Forest consumed manor, manor consumed forest. Both metabolized into a system treating death as input. The Wild Hunt has extended patrol range toward the Lantern Road farther than any prior generation.

Wild Hunt contact with trade convoys creates an unprecedented classification problem for Harbor Wardens. Necrotic entities are not smuggled goods or cursed artifacts -- they are active hostile process attached to material. The Quarantine Ledger's four-tier system was designed for objects, not biological intelligences replicating institutional structure in bark and bone.

The Thornwood Lich retains Lord Harren inside a system he created. Oath-breaking inverted: institution consuming the oath-swearer. The Shrine of the First Claw opposes precisely this.

Substrate logic (crystal-mediated necrotic ecology) is a Quarantine Ledger concern. Crystal-mediated phenomena are flagged in hazard tables regardless of origin.

Standing guidance to Sand-Sea Carters' Guild: any convoy reporting necrotic contact on the northern route triggers Tier Two inspection at the Reach boundary.
